<p> </p>
<p><strong>Itinerary </strong></p>
<p><strong>Day 1 (Saturday) </strong>Fly/train to Geneva. Transfer to Chamonix (1 hr) by coach with an opportunity to catch your first sightings of Mont Blanc.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 (Sunday) </strong>Embark on one of the inspirational walks (unguided) among the spruce forests, stunning glaciers and rocky peaks. The area is well sign posted with diverse walking trails suitable for all families. We recommend taking the first Grand Montets cable car and walking to the Glacier Argentière to return via the Réfuge Chalet de Lognan.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 (Monday) </strong>Enjoy the breathtaking views from the best vantage point on a tandem paraglide (optional). This often lands in the Savoy area, next to the Hotel La Folie Douce! For those who like to stay grounded, discover one of the numerous hiking trails in the area and enjoy the local flora and fauna.</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 (Tuesday) </strong>Slow down the pace for the last day and take a day to discover the shops of <a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a>. Enjoy lunch at one of the many cafés or brasseries then indulge on one of the fabulous ice cream parlours or patisseries, most with delicious macaroons on offer!</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 (Wednesday) </strong>The crowning highlight of your holiday, a scenic rail journey to <a data-udi="umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2e09d5bd5fae466db4b3c37d49150722}" title="Zermatt">Zermatt</a> via the famous Mont Blanc Express (approx. 4 hours connecting train to Martigny). Meandering through the Chamonix valley towards Chatelard and Martigny (three train changes), pass stunning scenery and encounter tunnels and high valley bridges on this red and white train.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 (Thursday) </strong>A must trip is an optional journey on the iconic Gornergrat railway for stunning views of the glaciers and the Matterhorn. Then take a wander around the picturesque village, soaking up the atmosphere.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 (Friday) </strong>Take a ramble along the Matterhorn trail through meadows down to Staffelalp before catching the gondola down from Furi and spend the afternoon at Zermatt’s museum with details of the first ascent of the Matterhorn.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 (Saturday) </strong>Guests staying 11 nights travel to <a data-udi="umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da}" title="Grindelwald">Grindelwald</a> (3 hrs with two changes), otherwise take the scenic rail transfer to the airport (3 ½ hrs to Zurich or 3 ¾ hrs to Geneva with up to two changes) for your flight home.</p>
<p><strong>Day 9 (Sunday) </strong>Not to be missed is Europe’s highest railway station, the Jungfraujoch. Savour the views of the Eiger whilst enjoying the leisurely train journey.</p>
<p><strong>Day 10 (Monday) </strong>Why not explore the many walking trails around this beautiful region. Take a bus to Grosse Scheidegg and meander back enjoying the magnificent views of the <a data-udi="umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771}" title="Bernese Oberland">Bernese Oberland</a>. Or for a more challenging walk, take the train to Kleine Scheidegg and walk the ‘Eiger trail’, which runs along the foot of the iconic Eiger North Wall.</p>
<p><strong>Day 11 (Tuesday)</strong> Staying local today, explore the beautiful village or for those feeling adventurous, have a go on Grindelwald-First’s Flyer zip wire!</p>
<p><strong>Day 12 (Wednesday) </strong>Guests staying 11 nights transfer to the airport (3 hrs to Zurich or 3 hrs ¾ to Geneva with two changes) for your flight home.</p>
<p><em>Please note that there is no luggage transfer on the train between resorts. Your Chamonix rep will help with luggage from the hotel to the train station, then again from the train station to your hotel in Zermatt/Grindelwald.</em></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>What’s Included</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Return scheduled flights from the UK </li>
<li>Airport transfer to Chamonix and rail transfers from Chamonix to the Swiss resorts and back to the airport</li>
<li>Scenic rail journey between Chamonix and Zermatt</li>
<li>7 or 11 nights in 3/4 star accommodation on half board catering with private facilities, plus a balcony in Zermatt and Grindelwald</li>
<li>Free daily packed lunch</li>
<li>Services of an Inghams rep in all resorts</li>
<li>Discount Swiss Travel Card worth £100 </li>
<li>Free use of local bus and train travel in Chamonix</li>
<li>Resort card for Chamonix</li>
<li>Walking opportunities in all resorts with the best mountain views</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Your Hotels</strong></p>
<p><strong>Chamonix </strong>(4 nights): <a data-udi="umb://document/29edcd3c50e4458281799c0617b52ba5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/29edcd3c50e4458281799c0617b52ba5}" title="La Folie Douce Hotel">Hotel La Folie Douce</a> ***/**** </p>
<p><strong>Zermatt </strong>(3 nights): <a data-udi="umb://document/8fa1210d0a794f8597980dec5856b80f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8fa1210d0a794f8597980dec5856b80f}" title="Hotel Alex">Hotel Alex</a> **** </p>
<p><strong>Grindelwald </strong>(4 nights): <a data-udi="umb://document/5ca846a0116f4035a41c0d484319c1dc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/5ca846a0116f4035a41c0d484319c1dc}" title="Hotel Derby">Hotel Derby</a> *** </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Excursion Highlights</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Aiguille du Midi cable car in Chamonix</li>
<li>Mer de Glace in Chamonix</li>
<li>Gornergrat Rack Railway in Zermatt</li>
<li>Matterhorn Glacier Paradise</li>
<li>Jungfraujoch to the 'Top of Europe'</li>
<li>James Bond Schilthorn</li>
</ul>
